Function Reference/is user option local « WordPress Codex
-----------

Check whether a usermeta key has to do with a particular blog.

Usage
-----

` <?php is_user_option_local( $key, $user_id, $blog_id ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$key` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) Usermeta key to check
    Default: *None*

 `$user_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) User ID whose key to check
    Default: current user

 `$blog_id` 
:   ([*integer*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#Integer "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*optional*) Blog ID against which to check
    Default: current user

Return Value
------------

 `` `(boolean)`{style="color:gray"} 
:   True if related, False if not

Examples
--------

